com.bbn.takml_sdk_android.mx_framework.request

Class MXListResourcesReply

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bbn.takml_sdk_android.mx_framework.request.MXListResourcesReply
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class MXListResourcesReply
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Reply to list the available resources in the MX framework.

    If requested, the MX framework can provide asynchronous updates about changes to the MX plugins and models that are made available or unavailable to the application.

    Note that the request to list MX framework resources does not have its own class. Instead, an MXRequest message is sent with its MXRequest.type set to MXRequest.Type.LIST_RESOURCES.

    • Method Detail

      • getPlugins

        public java.util.Set<java.lang.String> getPlugins()
        Get the list of plugins available in the MX framework, stylized as labels.

        To be more informational, the list of plugins is given as a list of strings, where each string is a label of the form "Plugin Name (Plugin ID)". Callers can use PredictionExecutor.pluginLabelToID(String) to extract the plugin ID from the label when needed to use that ID in a request to the MX framework.

        Returns:
        the list of plugins available in the MX framework, stylized as labels.

      • getModels

        public java.util.Set<java.lang.String> getModels()
        Get the list of models available in the MX framework, stylized as labels.

        To be more informational, the list of models is given as a list of strings, where each string is a label of the form "Model Name (Location)". Callers can use PredictionExecutor.modelLabelToName(String) to extract the model filename from the label when needed to use that filename in a request to the MX framework.

        Returns:
        the list of models available in the MX framework, stylized as labels.
